description: Number of non-unitary but squarefree divisors of n!. Also number of unitary but not-squarefree divisors of n!.
example: n=10, 10!=2.2.2.2.2.2.2.2.3.3.3.3.5.5.7=256.81.25.7, it has 270 divisors,16 unitary and 16 are squarefree; overlap={1,7}.Set {2,3,5,6,10,14,15,21,30,35,42,70,105,210} represents the squarefree not-unitary divisors of 10!, so a(10)=14.
author: _Labos Elemer_, Aug 10 2000
